@ghiculescu I don't think this will work quite right. On the first hit to the site you will get a nonce that is completely random and then the next hit for that session will get the session_id in the nonce and they won't match.  Mostly a problem with Turbo since the frame will get the random nonce and any subsequent requests will get something different.

My suggestion is to just initialize the session by doing something like...

```
config.content_security_policy_nonce_generator = ->(request) { request.session[:nonce] ||= SecureRandom.hex(16) }
```

